      <h1 class='title'>Housing (Northern Ireland) Order 1983 [H.L.]983/1118 (N.I. 15))</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc321-2GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_321gc' title='Col. 321GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c321GC' name='column_321gc' href='#column_321gc' rel='bookmark'>321GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04079'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_690' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        5 (1) In Article 24 (interpretation), amend paragraph (3) (meaning of member of another's family) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04080'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_691' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) After "spouse" insert ", civil partner".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04081'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_692' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) After "marriage" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04082'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_693' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) After "live together as husband and wife" insert "or as if they were civil partners".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04083'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_694' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        6 (1) Amend Article 26 (succession on death of tenant) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04084'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_695' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (2)(a), after "spouse" insert "or civil partner".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04085'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_696' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraph (3)(a), after "spouse" insert "or civil partner".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04086'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_697' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) In paragraph (4), for "paragraph (4A)" substitute "paragraphs (4A) and (4B)".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04087'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_698' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) After paragraph (4A) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(4B) A tenant to whom the tenancy was assigned in pursuance of an order under any of the following provisions of the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) Part 2 of Schedule (<i>Financial relief in the High Court or a county court etc.: Northern Ireland</i>); or</li>
        <li>(b) paragraph 9(2) or (3) of Schedule (<i>Financial relief in Northern Ireland after overseas dissolution etc. of a civil partnership</i>),</li></ol>
        is a successor only if the other civil partner was a successor.</q>
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_322gc' title='Col. 322GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c322GC' name='column_322gc' href='#column_322gc' rel='bookmark'>322GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04088'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_699' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        7 In Article 32 (assignments), in paragraph (1), after sub-paragraph (a) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(aa) the assignment is made in pursuance of an order made under Part 2 of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in the High Court or a county court etc.: Northern Ireland</span>), or paragraph 9(2) or (3) of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in Northern Ireland after overseas dissolution etc. of a civil partnership</span>), to the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>; or".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04089'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_700' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        8 In Article 33 (other disposals), in paragraph (2), after sub-paragraph (a) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(aa) the vesting or other disposal is in pursuance of an order made under Part 2 of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in the High Court or a county court etc.: Northern Ireland</span>), or paragraph 9(2) or (3) of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in Northern Ireland after overseas dissolution etc. of a civil partnership</span>), to the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>; or".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04090'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_701' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        9 In Article 94 (subletting or assignment), in paragraph (2), after "1978" insert "or Part 2 of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in the High Court or a county court etc.: Northern Ireland</span>), or paragraph 9(2) or (3) of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in Northern Ireland after overseas dissolution etc. of a civil partnership</span>), to the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04091'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_702' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        10 In Schedule 3 (grounds for possession of dwelling-houses let under secure tenancies), in Ground 2A&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a married couple or" substitute "a married couple, a couple who are civil partners of each other", and</li>
        <li>(b) after "as husband and wife" insert "or a couple living together as if they were civil partners".</li></ol>
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
